p({
"class":"foam.core.reflow.Flow",
"name":"manual:ExtendedMarkdown",
"version":2,
"script":
"""[
	{

		"flowName": "markdown1",
		"cmd": "markdown",
		"value": {
			"class": "foam.core.reflow.Markdown",
			"markdown": "# FLOW Markdown - Extended Features\\u000a\\u000aThis document covers the extended features available in FLOW Markdown beyond standard markdown syntax. These features enable interactive documentation, searchable sections, glossaries, permission-based content, and live code examples.\\u000a\\u000a## Table of Contents System\\u000a\\u000aThe TOC system provides automatic table of contents generation with optional section numbering.\\u000a\\u000a### Basic Usage\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<toc></toc>\\u000a\\u000a<h1>Introduction</h1>\\u000a<p>Some content...</p>\\u000a\\u000a<h2>Background</h2>\\u000a<p>More content...</p>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a### Numbered Sections\\u000a\\u000aEnable hierarchical numbering with `<tocconfig>`:\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<tocconfig index></tocconfig>\\u000a<toc></toc>\\u000a\\u000a<h1>Introduction</h1>\\u000a<h2>Background</h2>\\u000a<h2>Overview</h2>\\u000a<h1>Getting Started</h1>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000aThis renders headings as:\\u000a- 1. Introduction\\u000a- 1.1. Background\\u000a- 1.2. Overview\\u000a- 2. Getting Started\\u000a\\u000a### TOC Attributes\\u000a\\u000a| Element | Attribute | Description |\\u000a|---------|-----------|-------------|\\u000a| `<tocconfig>` | `index` | Enables hierarchical numbering on headings |\\u000a| `<toc>` | `title` | Custom title (default: \\"Table of Contents\\"). Set empty to hide. |\\u000a\\u000a### Heading Levels\\u000a\\u000aFour heading levels are supported: `<h1>`, `<h2>`, `<h3>`, `<h4>`. Each heading automatically generates an anchor ID for deep linking from the TOC.\\u000a\\u000a### Composable Documents\\u000a\\u000aThe TOC system works across included documents:\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<!-- book.md -->\\u000a<tocconfig index></tocconfig>\\u000a<toc></toc>\\u000a<include src=\\"chapter1.md\\"></include>\\u000a<include src=\\"chapter2.md\\"></include>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000aHeadings from all included files are collected and numbered correctly.\\u000a\\u000a## Searchable Sections\\u000a\\u000aThe section system wraps content into searchable, filterable units with their own headings.\\u000a\\u000a### Basic Usage\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<search></search>\\u000a<searchcount></searchcount>\\u000a\\u000a<section1 title=\\"Introduction\\">\\u000a  This is the intro section content.\\u000a</section1>\\u000a\\u000a<section2 title=\\"Getting Started\\">\\u000a  More content here.\\u000a</section2>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a### Section Elements\\u000a\\u000a| Element | Description |\\u000a|---------|-------------|\\u000a| `<section1>` | Level 1 section (like h1) |\\u000a| `<section2>` | Level 2 section (like h2) |\\u000a| `<section3>` | Level 3 section (like h3) |\\u000a| `<section4>` | Level 4 section (like h4) |\\u000a| `<search>` | Search input field |\\u000a| `<searchcount>` | Displays \\"Showing X of Y sections\\" |\\u000a\\u000a### Search Behavior\\u000a\\u000a- Typing in the search box filters sections in real-time\\u000a- Sections whose title or content match the query remain visible\\u000a- Non-matching sections are hidden\\u000a- Empty query shows all sections\\u000a- Search is case-insensitive\\u000a\\u000a### Search with Label\\u000a\\u000aLabels can be added inline:\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000aFilter: <search placeholder=\\"Search documentation...\\"></search>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a### Combined with TOC\\u000a\\u000aSections work with the TOC indexing system:\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<tocconfig index></tocconfig>\\u000a<search></search>\\u000a<searchcount></searchcount>\\u000a<toc></toc>\\u000a\\u000a<section1 title=\\"Introduction\\">\\u000a  Content here...\\u000a</section1>\\u000a\\u000a<section2 title=\\"Background\\">\\u000a  More content...\\u000a</section2>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a## Glossary System\\u000a\\u000aThe glossary system provides inline term definitions with popup lookups and auto-generated glossaries.\\u000a\\u000a### Defining Terms\\u000a\\u000aUse `<def>` to define terms:\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<def term=\\"DAO\\" definition=\\"Data Access Object. Provides CRUD operations for data storage.\\"></def>\\u000a<def term=\\"FOAM\\" definition=\\"Feature-Oriented Active Modeller.\\" source=\\"foam-framework.github.io\\"></def>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a### Referencing Terms\\u000a\\u000aUse `<term>` to create clickable references:\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<p>The <term term=\\"FOAM\\"></term> framework uses <term term=\\"DAO\\"></term>s for data access.</p>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000aClicking a term displays a popup with its definition.\\u000a\\u000a### Term Attributes\\u000a\\u000a| Element | Attribute | Description |\\u000a|---------|-----------|-------------|\\u000a| `<def>` | `term` | The term being defined (required) |\\u000a| `<def>` | `definition` | The definition text (required) |\\u000a| `<def>` | `source` | Optional source or citation |\\u000a| `<term>` | `term` | The term to look up (required) |\\u000a\\u000a### Rendering a Glossary\\u000a\\u000aUse `<glossary>` to render all defined terms alphabetically:\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<!-- Define terms anywhere in the document -->\\u000a<def term=\\"API\\" definition=\\"Application Programming Interface.\\"></def>\\u000a<def term=\\"REST\\" definition=\\"Representational State Transfer.\\"></def>\\u000a\\u000a<!-- Render the glossary -->\\u000a<glossary></glossary>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a### Container Style\\u000a\\u000aDefinitions can be grouped inside the glossary tag:\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<glossary>\\u000a  <def term=\\"DAO\\" definition=\\"Data Access Object.\\"></def>\\u000a  <def term=\\"View\\" definition=\\"A reactive UI component.\\"></def>\\u000a</glossary>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a### Composable Definitions\\u000a\\u000aTerms defined in included documents are collected:\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<!-- chapter1.md -->\\u000a<def term=\\"DAO\\" definition=\\"Data Access Object.\\"></def>\\u000a<p>A <term term=\\"DAO\\"></term> provides CRUD operations...</p>\\u000a\\u000a<!-- chapter2.md -->\\u000a<def term=\\"MDAO\\" definition=\\"In-memory DAO.\\"></def>\\u000a<p>For testing, use <term term=\\"MDAO\\"></term>...</p>\\u000a\\u000a<!-- book.md -->\\u000a<include src=\\"chapter1.md\\"></include>\\u000a<include src=\\"chapter2.md\\"></include>\\u000a<glossary></glossary>  <!-- Collects DAO and MDAO -->\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a## Permissioned Content\\u000a\\u000aConditionally display content based on user permissions.\\u000a\\u000a### Basic Usage\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<permissioned permission=\\"menu.admin.addUsers\\">\\u000a  <h2>Adding Users</h2>\\u000a  <p>To add a new user, click the Add User button...</p>\\u000a</permissioned>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a### Multiple Permissions (ANY)\\u000a\\u000aShow content if user has at least one permission:\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<permissioned permission=\\"admin.users, admin.roles\\">\\u000a  <p>User management options...</p>\\u000a</permissioned>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a### Multiple Permissions (ALL)\\u000a\\u000aShow content only if user has all permissions:\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<permissioned permission=\\"admin.users, admin.roles\\" require=\\"all\\">\\u000a  <p>Advanced user-role configuration...</p>\\u000a</permissioned>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a### Negated Permissions\\u000a\\u000aShow content when user does NOT have the permission:\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<permissioned permission=\\"premium.features\\" negate>\\u000a  <p>Upgrade to Premium to access this feature.</p>\\u000a</permissioned>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a### Permissioned Attributes\\u000a\\u000a| Attribute | Description |\\u000a|-----------|-------------|\\u000a| `permission` | Permission ID(s) to check. Comma-separated for multiple. (required) |\\u000a| `require` | `\\"any\\"` (default) or `\\"all\\"`. Whether user needs any or all permissions. |\\u000a| `negate` | If present, inverts the check (shows content if user LACKS permission). |\\u000a\\u000a### Security Note\\u000a\\u000aContent is completely omitted from the DOM if the permission check fails. Unauthorized users cannot inspect page source to see hidden content.\\u000a\\u000a## Live Code Examples\\u000a\\u000aThe `<example>` element provides live, editable code examples with output.\\u000a\\u000a### Basic Usage\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<example>\\u000alog('Hello, World!');\\u000a</example>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a### Available Functions\\u000a\\u000a| Function | Description |\\u000a|----------|-------------|\\u000a| `log(...)` | Output text/values (like console.log) |\\u000a| `add(...)` | Add elements to output |\\u000a| `br()` | Add a line break |\\u000a| `start(tag)` | Start building an element |\\u000a| `tag(name)` | Alias for start() |\\u000a| `E(nodeName)` | Create a FOAM element |\\u000a\\u000a### Examples\\u000a\\u000a**Simple output:**\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<example>\\u000alog('The answer is:', 6 * 7);\\u000a</example>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a**Multiple lines:**\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<example>\\u000alog('Line 1');\\u000alog('Line 2');\\u000alog('Sum:', 1 + 2 + 3);\\u000a</example>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a**Building elements:**\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<example>\\u000astart('div').\\u000a  style({color: 'blue', fontWeight: 'bold'}).\\u000a  add('Styled text').\\u000aend();\\u000a</example>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a**Using FOAM classes:**\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<example>\\u000afoam.CLASS({\\u000a  name: 'Person',\\u000a  properties: ['name', 'age']\\u000a});\\u000a\\u000avar p = Person.create({name: 'John', age: 30});\\u000alog('Name:', p.name);\\u000alog('Age:', p.age);\\u000a</example>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a### Code Editing\\u000a\\u000aThe code in examples is editable. Changes are executed automatically, allowing readers to experiment with the code.\\u000a\\u000a## Combining Features\\u000a\\u000aThese features can be combined for rich documentation:\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<tocconfig index></tocconfig>\\u000a\\u000a<!-- Glossary definitions -->\\u000a<def term=\\"DAO\\" definition=\\"Data Access Object.\\"></def>\\u000a<def term=\\"MDAO\\" definition=\\"In-memory DAO implementation.\\"></def>\\u000a\\u000a<!-- Search and navigation -->\\u000aSearch: <search></search>\\u000a<searchcount></searchcount>\\u000a<toc></toc>\\u000a\\u000a<!-- Content sections -->\\u000a<section1 title=\\"Introduction\\">\\u000a  <p>This guide covers <term term=\\"DAO\\"></term> usage in FOAM.</p>\\u000a</section1>\\u000a\\u000a<section2 title=\\"Basic Usage\\">\\u000a  <example>\\u000a  var dao = foam.dao.ArrayDAO.create();\\u000a  log('Created DAO');\\u000a  </example>\\u000a</section2>\\u000a\\u000a<section2 title=\\"Advanced Topics\\">\\u000a  <permissioned permission=\\"developer\\">\\u000a    <p>Internal implementation details...</p>\\u000a  </permissioned>\\u000a</section2>\\u000a\\u000a<!-- Collected glossary at end -->\\u000a<glossary></glossary>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a## Embedding FOAM Classes\\u000a\\u000aThe `<foam>` tag allows embedding any FOAM class directly in markdown.\\u000a\\u000a### Basic Usage\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<foam class=\\"foam.u2.DetailView\\" data=\\"myObject\\"></foam>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a### Syntax\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<foam class=\\"fully.qualified.ClassName\\" attribute1=\\"value1\\" attribute2=\\"value2\\"></foam>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000aThe `class` attribute specifies the FOAM class to instantiate. All other attributes are passed as constructor arguments to the class.\\u000a\\u000a### Examples\\u000a\\u000a**Embed an animated clock:**\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<foam class=\\"foam.core.reflow.Clock\\" x=110 y=110></foam>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a**Embed a custom view:**\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<foam class=\\"com.myapp.MyCustomView\\"></foam>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a**Pass properties:**\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<foam class=\\"foam.u2.TextField\\" data=\\"initialValue\\" placeholder=\\"Enter text...\\"></foam>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a**Embed a controller:**\\u000a\\u000a```html\\u000a<foam class=\\"com.myapp.DashboardController\\" mode=\\"compact\\"></foam>\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a### Use Cases\\u000a\\u000a- Embed interactive widgets in documentation\\u000a- Include application components in help pages\\u000a- Create live demos of FOAM views\\u000a- Build hybrid static/dynamic documents\\u000a\\u000a### Error Handling\\u000a\\u000aIf the specified class is not found, the tag displays an error message:\\u000a\\u000a```\\u000aUNKNOWN CLASS: some.invalid.ClassName\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a## Quick Reference\\u000a\\u000a| Element | Purpose |\\u000a|---------|---------|\\u000a| `<tocconfig index>` | Enable section numbering |\\u000a| `<toc>` | Render table of contents |\\u000a| `<h1>` - `<h4>` | Heading levels |\\u000a| `<section1>` - `<section4>` | Searchable section levels |\\u000a| `<search>` | Search input field |\\u000a| `<searchcount>` | Section count display |\\u000a| `<def>` | Define a glossary term |\\u000a| `<term>` | Reference a glossary term |\\u000a| `<glossary>` | Render all definitions |\\u000a| `<permissioned>` | Permission-gated content |\\u000a| `<example>` | Live code example |\\u000a| `<include>` | Include another document |\\u000a\\u000a---\\u000a\\u000a**End of Extended Features Documentation**"
		},
		"border": {
			"oldTitleStyle_": "h300"
		},
		"padding_st": "16px"
	}
]""",
"created":"2026-02-03T20:36:20.296Z",
"lastModified":"2026-02-03T20:36:20.296Z",
"lastRun":"2026-02-03T20:16:41.754Z"
})
p({
"class":"foam.core.reflow.Flow",
"name":"manual:ExtendedMarkdownExample",
"version":9,
"script":
"""[
	{

		"flowName": "markdown1",
		"cmd": "markdown",
		"value": {
			"class": "foam.core.reflow.Markdown",
			"markdown": "<tocconfig index></tocconfig>\\u000a\\u000a<span style=\\"font-size: x-large\\">Sample Extended Markdown</span>\\u000a\\u000a<!-- Search and navigation -->\\u000aSearch: <search></search>\\u000a<searchcount></searchcount>\\u000a<toc></toc>\\u000a\\u000a<!-- Content sections -->\\u000a<section1 title=\\"Introduction\\">\\u000a  <p>This guide covers <term term=\\"DAO\\"></term> usage in FOAM.</p>\\u000a</section1>\\u000a\\u000a<section2 title=\\"Basic Usage\\">\\u000a<example>\\u000avar dao = foam.dao.ArrayDAO.create();\\u000alog('Created DAO');\\u000a</example>\\u000a</section2>\\u000a\\u000a<section2 title=\\"Advanced Topics\\">\\u000a  <permissioned permission=\\"developer\\">\\u000a    <p>Internal implementation details...</p>\\u000a  </permissioned>\\u000a</section2>\\u000a\\u000a<!-- Collected glossary at end -->\\u000a<glossary>\\u000a  <def term=\\"DAO\\" definition=\\"Data Access Object.\\"></def>\\u000a  <def term=\\"MDAO\\" definition=\\"In-memory DAO implementation.\\"></def>\\u000a</glossary>"
		},
		"border": {
			"oldTitleStyle_": "h300"
		},
		"padding_st": "16px"
	}
]""",
"created":"2026-02-03T20:36:37.605Z",
"lastModified":"2026-02-03T20:36:37.605Z",
