})
p({
"class":"foam.core.reflow.Flow",
"name":"manual:Markdown",
"version":14,
"script":
"""[
	{

		"flowName": "markdown1",
		"cmd": "markdown",
		"value": {
			"class": "foam.core.reflow.Markdown",
			"markdown": "# FLOW Markdown - Supported Features\\u000a\\u000aThis document demonstrates all the markdown features supported by the FLOW Markdown command.\\u000a\\u000a## Headings\\u000a\\u000a# Heading 1\\u000a## Heading 2\\u000a### Heading 3\\u000a#### Heading 4\\u000a##### Heading 5\\u000a###### Heading 6\\u000a\\u000aNote: H1 and H2 headings automatically include a horizontal rule below them.\\u000a\\u000a## Text Formatting\\u000a\\u000a**Bold text using double asterisks**\\u000a\\u000a__Bold text using double underscores__\\u000a\\u000a*Italic text using single asterisk*\\u000a\\u000a_Italic text using single underscore_\\u000a\\u000a~~Strikethrough text using double tildes~~\\u000a\\u000a`Inline code using backticks`\\u000a\\u000aYou can also combine formatting: **bold with _nested italic_** text.\\u000a\\u000a## Code Blocks\\u000a\\u000aFenced code blocks with language specification:\\u000a\\u000a```javascript\\u000afunction greet(name) {\\u000a  console.log(\\"Hello, \\" + name + \\"!\\");\\u000a  return true;\\u000a}\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a```python\\u000adef calculate_sum(a, b):\\u000a    return a + b\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a```\\u000aPlain text code block without language\\u000a```\\u000a\\u000a## Lists\\u000a\\u000a### Unordered Lists\\u000a\\u000aUsing hyphens:\\u000a- First item\\u000a- Second item\\u000a- Third item\\u000a\\u000aUsing asterisks:\\u000a* Alpha\\u000a* Beta\\u000a* Gamma\\u000a\\u000aUsing plus signs:\\u000a+ Red\\u000a+ Green\\u000a+ Blue\\u000a\\u000a### Nested Lists\\u000a\\u000a- Top level item\\u000a    - Nested item 1\\u000a    - Nested item 2\\u000a        - Deeply nested item\\u000a- Another top level item\\u000a\\u000a### Ordered Lists\\u000a\\u000a1. First step\\u000a2. Second step\\u000a3. Third step\\u000a\\u000aStarting from a different number:\\u000a5. Fifth item\\u000a6. Sixth item\\u000a7. Seventh item\\u000a\\u000a### Mixed Lists\\u000a\\u000a1. Ordered item one\\u000a    - Nested unordered\\u000a    - Another nested\\u000a2. Ordered item two\\u000a\\u000a## Blockquotes\\u000a\\u000a> This is a blockquote.\\u000a> It can span multiple lines.\\u000a> \\u000a> And contain multiple paragraphs.\\u000a\\u000a> Single line blockquote\\u000a\\u000a## Horizontal Rules\\u000a\\u000aThree or more hyphens:\\u000a\\u000a---\\u000a\\u000aThree or more asterisks:\\u000a\\u000a***\\u000a\\u000aThree or more underscores:\\u000a\\u000a___\\u000a\\u000a## Links\\u000a\\u000a[FOAM3 Repository](https://github.com/kgrgreer/foam3)\\u000a\\u000a[Google](https://www.google.com)\\u000a\\u000a[Link with no protocol](example.com)\\u000a\\u000a## Images\\u000a\\u000a![FOAM Logo](https://via.placeholder.com/150x50/0066cc/ffffff?text=FOAM)\\u000a\\u000a![Placeholder Image](https://via.placeholder.com/300x200)\\u000a\\u000a![Image with title](https://via.placeholder.com/200 \\"This is a title\\")\\u000a\\u000a## Tables\\u000a\\u000aBasic table:\\u000a\\u000a| Header 1 | Header 2 | Header 3 |\\u000a|----------|----------|----------|\\u000a| Cell 1   | Cell 2   | Cell 3   |\\u000a| Cell 4   | Cell 5   | Cell 6   |\\u000a\\u000aTable with alignment:\\u000a\\u000a| Left Aligned | Center Aligned | Right Aligned |\\u000a|:-------------|:--------------:|--------------:|\\u000a| Left         | Center         | Right         |\\u000a| Text         | Text           | Text          |\\u000a| 1            | 2              | 3             |\\u000a\\u000aTable with complex content:\\u000a\\u000a| Feature | Supported | Notes |\\u000a|---------|:---------:|-------|\\u000a| Bold | ✓ | Use `**` or `__` |\\u000a| Italic | ✓ | Use `*` or `_` |\\u000a| Code | ✓ | Use backticks |\\u000a\\u000a## HTML Support\\u000a\\u000a### HTML Comments\\u000a\\u000a<!-- This is an HTML comment and won't be visible -->\\u000a\\u000aComments are parsed but not rendered in the output.\\u000a\\u000a### Block-Level HTML\\u000a\\u000a<div class=\\"custom-container\\" id=\\"main\\">\\u000a  This is a custom div with attributes.\\u000a</div>\\u000a\\u000a<section style=\\"background: #f0f0f0; padding: 20px;\\">\\u000a  A styled section element.\\u000a</section>\\u000a\\u000aSelf-closing tags:\\u000a<br/>\\u000a<hr/>\\u000a\\u000a### Inline HTML\\u000a\\u000aThis paragraph contains <span style=\\"color: red;\\">red text</span> and <strong>bold HTML</strong>.\\u000a\\u000aYou can use <code>inline code tags</code> and <em>emphasis tags</em>.\\u000a\\u000aBoolean attributes work too: <input type=\\"checkbox\\" checked disabled/>\\u000a\\u000a### Nested HTML\\u000a\\u000a<div class=\\"outer\\">\\u000a  <div class=\\"inner\\">\\u000a    <p>Nested HTML elements</p>\\u000a  </div>\\u000a</div>\\u000a\\u000a## Complex Examples\\u000a\\u000a### Mixing Markdown and HTML\\u000a\\u000a<div style=\\"border: 2px solid blue; padding: 10px;\\">\\u000a\\u000a# Markdown Heading Inside HTML\\u000a\\u000aThis **markdown** formatting works _inside_ HTML blocks!\\u000a\\u000a- List item 1\\u000a- List item 2\\u000a\\u000a</div>\\u000a\\u000a### Table with Formatted Content\\u000a\\u000a| Syntax | Output | Description |\\u000a|--------|--------|-------------|\\u000a| `**bold**` | **bold** | Bold text |\\u000a| `*italic*` | *italic* | Italic text |\\u000a| `` `code` `` | `code` | Inline code |\\u000a| `~~strike~~` | ~~strike~~ | Strikethrough |\\u000a\\u000a### Comprehensive Example\\u000a\\u000aHere's a comprehensive example combining multiple features:\\u000a\\u000a1. **Getting Started**\\u000a    - Install FOAM3\\u000a    - Read the [documentation](https://github.com/kgrgreer/foam3)\\u000a    - Write your first app\\u000a2. **Building Features**\\u000a     ```javascript\\u000a    foam.CLASS({\\u000a      package: 'com.example',\\u000a      name: 'MyClass',\\u000a      properties: ['name', 'value']\\u000a    });\\u000a     ```\\u000a3. **Testing**\\u000a    > Remember to test your code thoroughly!\\u000a    > Unit tests are _essential_ for quality.\\u000a\\u000a---\\u000a\\u000a## Escape Sequences\\u000a\\u000aCurrently, the parser handles special characters literally. To display markdown syntax as text, you can use code formatting:\\u000a\\u000a- To show asterisks: `**not bold**`\\u000a<!-- - To show backticks: `` `code` `` TODO: Doesn't work -->\\u000a- To show brackets: `[not a link](url)`\\u000a\\u000a## Limitations and Notes\\u000a\\u000a1. **Inline HTML parsing**: HTML inside inline content is parsed but attributes are extracted as-is\\u000a2. **Nested formatting**: Some complex nested formatting may have limitations\\u000a3. **Line breaks**: Use blank lines to separate paragraphs\\u000a4. **List indentation**: Nested lists require 4 spaces of indentation\\u000a5. **Table cell content**: Supports inline markdown formatting within cells\\u000a\\u000a---\\u000a\\u000a## Quick Reference\\u000a\\u000a| Feature | Syntax | Example |\\u000a|---------|--------|---------|\\u000a| Heading | `# H1` to `###### H6` | # Heading |\\u000a| Bold | `**text**` or `__text__` | **bold** |\\u000a| Italic | `*text*` or `_text_` | *italic* |\\u000a| Code | `` `code` `` | `code` |\\u000a| Link | `[text](url)` | [link](url) |\\u000a| Image | `![alt](url)` | ![img](image1) |\\u000a| Blockquote | `> quote` | > quote |\\u000a| List | `- item` or `1. item` | - item |\\u000a| HR | `---` or `***` or `___` | --- |\\u000a| Strikethrough | `~~text~~` | ~~text~~ |\\u000a| HTML | `<b>text</b>` | <b>text</b> |\\u000a\\u000a<!-- | Table | `\\\\| col \\\\|` | \\\\| A \\\\| B \\\\| | TODO: doesn't work -->\\u000a \\u000a---\\u000a\\u000a**End of Documentation**\\u000a\\u000aThis markdown file showcases all supported features of the FLOW Markdown command."
		},
		"border": {
			"oldTitleStyle_": "h300"
		},
		"padding_st": "16px"
	},
	{

		"flowName": "image1",
		"cmd": "image",
		"value": {
			"class": "foam.core.reflow.Image",
			"imageData": "data:image/png;base64,"
		},
		"border": {
			"oldTitleStyle_": "h300"
		},
		"shown": false,
		"padding_st": "16px"
	}
]""",
"created":"2026-02-03T20:36:05.630Z",
